http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Six-child-labourers-rescued-in-Mulbagal/article13996055.ece

In a joint operation, the District Child Protection Cell and Labour Department officials rescued six child labourers in Mulbagal on Tuesday.They were found working in workshops, garages and some other places where employment of children is prohibited under Child Labour Act.Two of them are below 14 years. All of them have been sent to the Children’s Home (Balamandira) in Kolar Gold Fields, Labour Inspector P.G. Balaji told The Hindu . “We had been observing these places for a few days and noticed that they had employed children,” he said.The owners of these places may be sent to jail for violating the law, he added.